                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004">Fol. ivr(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and hand <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#83v" facs="088">Fol. 83v</locus><desc>Talismanic Symbol (partial-margin artist)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#168r" facs="172">Fol. 168r</locus><desc>man with stripped garment (partial-margin artist)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #8r #23v #34r #42r #48r #57v #69r #78r #110v #114r #127v #141r #160r" facs="005 012 028 038 046 052 062 073 082 115 118 132 145 164">folss. 1r, 8r, 23v, 34r, 42r, 48r, 57v, 69r, 78r, 110v, 114r, 127v, 141r, 160r, </locus> (harägs, sometimes just outlined in pencil);
                    <locus target="#1r #7v #77v #113v #120r #148v #152r #154v" facs="005 012 082 118 124 153 156 159">1r, 7v, 77v, 113v, 120r, 148v, 152r, 154v, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#104v" facs="109">104v, </locus> (multiple full stops connected by alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#157r" facs="161">157r, </locus> (a line of full stops);
                    <locus target="#159r" facs="163">159r</locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots between lines of full stops).
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                  <item xml:id="a1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fols. iiv(erso), iiir(ecto)</locus> The nine feast days of Our Lord and the Apostles’ feast days, in faded ink
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="a2">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus> Beginning of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1693John">Gospel of John</title>
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="a3">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#168v" facs="173">Fol. 168v</locus> The Lucky and Unlucky Days of the Year, in a very clear hand.
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐሳበ፡ ጽንዕት፡ ወጽንጽንት፡ መሥከረም፡ እስከ፡ ፲፭፡ ጸንዕት፡ የቀረው፡ ጽንጽንት። ጥቅምት፡ እስከ፡ ፲፫፡ ጽንዕት፡ የቀረው፡ ጽንጽንት፡...</foreign>
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus> a couple of words
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e2">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iiiv(erso)" facs="001 002 004">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iiiv(erso)</locus>: blank
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e3">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#39v" facs="044">Fol. 39v</locus>: washed of text, which is still faintly visible, to prepare for painting
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e4">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#63v" facs="068">Fol. 63v</locus> cross-shaped symbol in right margin, marks the midpoint of the psalms
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e5">
                  <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–14
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e6">
                  <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5v #34v #39r #50v #55v" facs="010 039 043 055 060">folss. 5v, 34v, 39r, 50v, 55v, </locus>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3v #6v #9r #10v #16r" facs="008 011 013 015 020">3v, 6v, 9r, 10v, 16r, </locus>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#143v" facs="148"> f. 143v, line 15</locus>), and in another case where the symbol (┴) is used (<locus target="#157r" facs="161"> f. 157r, line 1</locus>)
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e7">
                  <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions,
                    the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#42v #55v #100r" facs="047 060 104">folss. 42v, 55v, 100r, </locus>).
                    Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#20r #40r #46r #60v" facs="024 044 050 065">20r, 40r, 46r, 60v</locus>).
                  </desc>
                  </item>

                  </list>
                  </additions>
